## 1. Data Contract (READ FIRST — exact shapes from real data)

The content lives in two globals defined in Hanasou’s `lessons.js`. Import that file as-is (copy it into the game repo, or fetch it; keep it as the single source). Shapes below are verified against the real file.

### `window.LEVELS` — the tier map (≈ JLPT N5→N3)

```js
window.LEVELS = [
  {
    id: "L1", name: "Level 1", title: "Foundations",
    blurb: "Survival Japanese — greetings, shopping & daily life · N5",
    tiers: [
      { name: "Beginner",     blurb: "...", themes: ["First contact", "Getting things"] },
      { name: "Intermediate", blurb: "...", themes: ["Doing things", "Daily life"] },
      // ...
    ],
  },
  // L2..L5
];
```

- A **theme** is a string. It joins `LEVELS` to `LESSONS` via `lesson.section === theme`.
- Difficulty ordering for stage unlocks = `LEVELS` array order (L1 easiest → L5 hardest), then tier order within a level.

### `window.LESSONS` — the content (58 lessons)

```js
window.LESSONS = [
  {
    id: "intro",
    section: "First contact",     // <-- matches a theme string in LEVELS
    title: "Hello & introductions",
    grammar: "X は Y です  ·  か",
    grammarNote: "...",
    vocab: [ { jp, romaji, en, pos }, ... ],
    sentences: [
      {
        en: "I am Tom.",
        jp: "わたしはトムです。",
        romaji: "watashi wa tomu desu.",
        hint: "...",                 // optional
        words: [                     // <-- THE KEY FIELD. pre-tokenized, ordered.
          { jp: "わたし", en: "I",       pos: "n"   },
          { jp: "は",     en: "[topic]", pos: "prt" },
          { jp: "トム",   en: "Tom",     pos: "n"   },
          { jp: "です",   en: "am",      pos: "cop" },
        ],
      },
      // ...
    ],
  },
  // ...
];
```

### `words[].pos` — the complete tag set (verified counts, whole corpus)

|pos   |meaning              |count|game role                                |
|------|---------------------|-----|-----------------------------------------|
|`n`   |noun                 |337  |socketable role word                     |
|`prt` |**particle**         |257  |**the connectors — core of the minigame**|
|`v`   |verb                 |219  |the **center** of the socket puzzle      |
|`cop` |copula (です etc.)     |101  |sentence-final, treated as fixed tail    |
|`adj` |adjective            |80   |socketable / modifier                    |
|`aux` |auxiliary (ください, ます…)|60   |sentence-final-ish                       |
|`adv` |adverb               |30   |free-floating                            |
|`expr`|set expression       |33   |whole-phrase, not socketed               |
|`conj`|conjunction          |20   |connector                                |

### `pos: "prt"` — the actual particle inventory (verified)

These are the ONLY particles that appear in the corpus, by frequency. The minigame’s particle picker must draw distractors from THIS set (don’t invent particles the learner hasn’t seen):

```
を(51) は(45) か(43) に(35) が(29) で(20) の(8) と(8)
まで(5) よ(2) も(2) な(2) って(2) ぐらい(2) より(1) ね(1) から(1)
```

**Note:** `か`, `よ`, `ね` are sentence-final/mood particles, not role-markers. Tag particles into two functional buckets at index time (see §4.3): **role-markers** (は が を に で と へ から まで の も) vs **sentence-final** (か よ ね な って). The socket puzzle only sockets role-markers; sentence-final particles render as a fixed tail.

### Content index to build at load

Build once on boot:

```js
// flat list of every sentence, tagged with its origin for stage filtering
sentences = [
  {
    sid,                 // stable id: `${lessonId}#${sentenceIndex}`
    lessonId, section,   // section = theme string
    levelId, tierName,   // resolved via LEVELS lookup
    en, jp, romaji, hint,
    words,               // the array above
    // derived:
    roleWords,           // words that get socketed (n/adj/adv content words preceding a role-marker)
    particles,           // ordered role-markers used, e.g. ["は","を"]
    verb,                // the v/cop/aux that anchors the sentence (usually last content slot)
    difficulty,          // int: # of role-markers + length heuristic (for ramping)
  },
  ...
]
```

Also build `wordPool` per stage = the set of unique `{jp,en,pos}` across that stage’s sentences (the pickup spawn table).

