## 2. Core gameplay (Vampire Survivors clone — get this right first)

Faithful VS clone. If a behavior isn’t specified here, **default to how Vampire Survivors does it.**

- **Input:** movement ONLY. Desktop = WASD/arrows or hold-mouse-to-move-toward-cursor. Mobile = virtual joystick (drag anywhere on left half of screen). Unify via Phaser pointer/keyboard input. There is **no aiming and no attack button** — weapons auto-fire.
- **Player:** stays roughly centered; world/camera scrolls. Has HP. Takes contact damage from enemies.
- **Auto-attack:** the equipped weapon(s) fire automatically on a timer toward nearest/relevant enemies. Upgrades increase damage, fire rate, count, area, add new weapons, and add passive auras around the player.
- **Enemies:** spawn from screen edges in escalating waves over a ~15–20 min run. Density ramps over time. See §6 bestiary for archetypes (each archetype = a movement AI).
- **XP:** killed enemies drop XP gems; collect by proximity. XP bar fills → **level-up** (triggers §4).
- **Run end:** boss spawns near the end of the run; defeating it = run clear → meta rewards + potential stage unlock.
- **Death:** run ends, return to meta screen.

**Juice (do not skip — this is “flashy pixel art”):** screenshake on big hits, hit-flash (tint white 1 frame), particle bursts on kills, XP-gem magnet sparkle, number popups, additive-blend glow on attacks, satisfying level-up freeze-frame with a vignette/zoom. Pixel-art sprites, sprite-sheet animation.

