## 3. Word collection (feeds the minigame)

- **Floor pickups:** rare, glowy word-tokens spawn on the ground (NOT every pickup — most ground drops are XP gems; word-tokens are loot-rare, like VS chests). Walking over one: adds `{jp,en,pos}` to the **run’s collected-word pool**, plays the word’s audio if available (fall back to device TTS), shows a brief floating JP+EN label.
- **Merch-Mule enemies:** a dedicated trash-mob type that, on death, drops a word-token. This gives the swarm purpose — players hunt Mules for vocab.
- **Collected pool is run-only.** It resets every run. It is the ONLY source the level-up minigame draws sentences from (with one fallback, §4.5).
- Spawn the stage’s `wordPool` weighted so the player tends to collect words that can actually *form* sentences together (bias toward words from the same sentences). Avoid handing out 12 unrelated nouns and no verb.

