## 6. Characters & enemies

### Characters (combat flavor ONLY — no content gating)

Playable girls = VS-style identity: starting weapon + passive + playstyle. They do **not** filter or restrict Japanese content (stages do that). Unlockable via meta-progression.

- **VTuber** — fast, wide-spread projectiles.
- **Cosplayer** — tanky, short-range melee sweep.
- **Idol** — rhythmic pulsing AoE.

### Enemies (behavior = AI; the comedy is in movement, never body type)

Each archetype is defined by a movement rule + combat quirk + visual tell so the swarm is readable at a glance. ~70% of the swarm should be plain fodder; personality types are seasoning.

|key            |name            |behavior (AI)                                 |quirk                                              |
|---------------|----------------|----------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
|`RushFan`      |Rushing Fan     |straight beeline at player (fodder bulk)      |basic                                              |
|`AnxiousOne`   |The Anxious One |rushes in, then flees before contact          |baits aim, wastes attacks                          |
|`TooCool`      |The Too-Cool One|runs at player **backwards**, hands in pockets|slow, ignores weak hits; brief untargetable “glint”|
|`CameraGremlin`|Camera Gremlin  |stops at range, “flashes”                     |flash whites out a screen region briefly           |
|`IdolWota`     |Idol-Wota       |rhythmic side-to-side concert sway            |hard to pin/hit                                    |
|`Lurker`       |Lurker          |hangs at edge, barely approaches              |powers up if ignored too long                      |
|`Glomper`      |Glomper         |slow, large, tanky                            |latches on contact, slows player                   |
|`MerchMule`    |Merch-Mule      |wanders, evasive                              |**drops a word-token on death**                    |

### Bosses (named characters; joke is the obsession, not the appearance)

One per stage, e.g. **“The Ultimate Collector”** — over-the-top super-fan with an absurd goal and a multi-phase fight. Write personality; never make body type the gag.

